            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&quot;The same would be true in a college programming class if the example code used that include.&quot; Heck no. The people you teach to don&apos;t know any better. They don&apos;t know what&apos;s appropriate and what&apos;s not: anything the professor writes is gospel taken on faith. Please, don&apos;t suggest any educators that this idiocy is warranted.&lt;/span&gt;

